      "writtenOn": "2026-03-03T07:48:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Any chance we can do that in a separate schema?\n\nMaybe something like \n\n```\n{\n  \"Name\": \"Override1\",\n  \"OverrideName\": \"FANBOARD$bus % 30 ADC\",\n  \"Label\": \"in0\",\n  \"Unit\": \"Amperes\",\n  \"Type\": \"UnitOverride\"\n}\n```\n\nNow `OverrideName` would be the `Name` for which the override is done, and `Label` for the label where we are overriding the unit.\n\nWhat do you think about it 😊",
      "revId": "6eb7017276078f4ca1212edef55cb7e2de80f2a5",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "a35306b2_a386eeb3",
        "filename": "schemas/legacy.json",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 835,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002134
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-03T09:57:43Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the suggestion!\nIf I understand correctly, you\u0027re proposing a separate override mechanism to:\n- Keep sensor definitions and overrides cleanly separated\n- Make it reusable across different sensor types (PSUSensor, HwmonTemp, etc.)\n- Enable extensibility to other properties beyond units\n- Provide a more generic solution that could be used by other sensor daemons\n\nThe implementation would require cross-Expose references (dbus-sensors doesn\u0027t \ncurrently support this), so it\u0027s more complex than the `{label}_Units` pattern. \nBut for better commonality and extensibility, I agree this is the better approach.\n\nOne question - you mentioned `UnitOverride` as the Type. If we want to extend \nthis to other properties (`scale`, `thresholds`, etc.) in the future, would a \ngeneric `Override` Type with optional properties be better? That way a single \nExpose could override multiple properties for the same target.\n\nWhat do you think?",
      "parentUuid": "f4ddd378_f1310342",
      "revId": "6eb7017276078f4ca1212edef55cb7e2de80f2a5",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5fb2902c_098f1887",
        "filename": "schemas/legacy.json",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 835,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001712
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-03-03T10:49:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e The implementation would require cross-Expose references (dbus-sensors doesn\u0027tcurrently support this), so it\u0027s more complex than the {label}_Units pattern.\n\nYes, maybe we can use something like `\"HasOverride\": \"Unit\"` property in the `PSUSensor` schema to tell it that it needs to query the override.\n\n\u003e One question - you mentioned UnitOverride as the Type. If we want to extend\nthis to other properties (scale, thresholds, etc.) in the future, would a\ngeneric Override Type with optional properties be better? That way a single\nExpose could override multiple properties for the same target.\n\nThe Scale, Thresholds and such are properties which can be configured while this patch overrides something which currently cannot be configured.\n\nFrom my perspective it would be best to handle much of the configuration / override logic in EM internally to avoid reactors having to query across multiple object paths and have to aggregate information.\n\nThat way EM could recognize an override, apply the changes, and the reactor would get a properties changed match and reconfigure. Or not have to deal with that at all if the override is applied before configuration is first exposed on D-Bus.\n\nBut as EM development is taking it\u0027s time, maybe we can consider temporary workarounds such as reactors querying for overrides for `scale`, `thresholds` and such configured separately.\n\nTo avoid creating disproportionate delay for otherwise straightforward changes like unit override. So i would agree making a generic `Override` Type could be a solution there.\n\n@spinler@us.ibm.com what do you think, is it better to configure the overrides separately to have a simple and reusable schema or better to go with current revision (Patchset 4)?",
      "parentUuid": "a35306b2_a386eeb3",
